==English==
===Etymology===
From the latin ''angulus'', an angle
===Adjective===
'''Angulate''' 
#Shaped with corners or angles;
#In [[botany]] and [[zoology]], the shape of [[stem]]s, [[leaf|leaves]] and [[wing]]s.
===Noun===
'''Angulation'''
#Measure of one's ability to get some from a woman wherein the age separation between the man and woman must be greater than 10 years to form an acute angle; right angulation can be achieved if the age difference is anywhere between 5 and 10 years.
===Verb===
'''Angulate'''
===Sentence===
#Dude, I heard your grandpa banged that kid's twenty year-old mom last night. That must have been some beast angulation.
#When you angulate well, you don't just skid through the turn; you shoot through it.
#Mrs. Harrell can tell you all about angulation.